
Classical combination: ./configure; make; make install should work on most systems.

This software was tested successfully before releasing version 0.9.2 on following systems:

1. Fedora 17 (i686-pc-linux-gnu/pulseaudio/pthread)

2. Solaris 11 (i386-pc-solaris2.11/pulseaudio/pthread). 
   Install "system/header" and "gcc-45" package before compiling.
   
3. OpenIndiana 151a7 (i386-pc-solaris2.11/oss/pthread). 
   Install "system/header", "gcc-45" and "system/header/header-audio"
   before compiling. Compiles without mouse support.
   
4. FreeBSD 9.1 (i386-unknown-freebsd9.1/oss/pthread).

5. Cygwin (i686-pc-cygwin/waveout and i686-pc-cygwin/oss/pthread).

6. MinGW32 (i686-pc-mingw32/waveout).

Successful compilation, but without audio testing was done also on following systems:

1. OpenBSD 5.1 (i386-unknown-openbsd5.1/oss/pthread).
2. NetBSD 6.0.1 (i386-unknown-netbsdelf6.0.1/oss/pthread).
